  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "AutoCAD Drafter",
  "description": "<p><strong>RESPONSIBILITY</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Utilises knowledge of various machines, engineering practices, mathematics, building materials and other physical sciences to complete drawings;</li>\n  <li>Verify that drawings are accurate, legible, and follow applicable industry codes;</li>\n  <li>Create detailed drawings as per clients’ specifications;</li>\n  <li>Work directly with project manager and 3D designer to develop drawings, schematics, and diagrams for projects;</li>\n  <li>Uses computer assisted design/drafting equipment and software to develop designs;</li>\n  <li>Creates and revises fabrication drawings;</li>\n  <li>Drafts detailed multi-view drawings of products;</li>\n  <li>Modify existing drawings to reflect necessary changes;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Self-motivated and able to work independently and on a team;</li>\n  <li>Detail oriented, organized with the ability to handle multiple ongoing projects and meet deadlines;</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of drafting standards, mathematics, and engineering technology;</li>\n  <li>The ability to pay attention to detail and follow work instructions;</li>\n  <li>Able to effectively communicate and work collaboratively with various departments such as project, production and designer;</li>\n  <li>Ability to work in a fast paced, high volume environment;</li>\n  <li>Degree or Diploma in Architectural or Civil Engineering or Building Information Technology</li>\n  <li>Minimium 1 year of relevant experience in construction industry</li>\n  <li>Proficient in AutoCAD, Sketch Up &amp; 3D Max</li>\n</ul>",
